Konvergensi dalam Peluang
Jika \(\{X_{n}\}\) adalah suatu barisan peubah acak (\(X_1, X_2, \ldots, X_{i}, \ldots\) dengan ukuran sampel adalah i) dan X adalah peubah acak, maka \(X_{n}\) konvergen dalam peluang ke X jika untuk tiap \(\varepsilon>0\),
\[
\begin{aligned}
\lim_{n\to\infty} P\left(|X_n-X|\geq\varepsilon\right)=0
\end{aligned}
\]
Atau,
\[
\begin{aligned}
\lim_{n\to\infty} P\left(|X_n-X|<\varepsilon\right)=1
\end{aligned}
\]
Dinotasikan:
\[
\begin{aligned}
X_n \ \xrightarrow{p}\ X .
\end{aligned}
\]

Konvergensi dalam Distribusi

Diberikan fungsi kumulatif \(X_n\) sebagai berikut. Tunjukkan \(X_{n}\) konvergen dalam distribusi ke \(\mathrm{Exponential}(1)\)!
\[
    \begin{equation}
    F_{X_n}(x)=
    \begin{cases}
    1-\left(1-\frac{1}{n}\right)^{nx} & \quad x > 0\\
    & \quad \\
    0 & \quad \text{lainnya}
    \end{cases}
    \end{equation}
\]
Cari limit dari fungsi kumulatif tersebut:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\lim_{n\to\infty}F_{X_n}(x)&=\lim_{n\to\infty}\left\{1-\left(1-\frac{1}{n}\right)^{nx}\right\} &  x > 0\\
&=1-\lim_{n\to\infty}\left(1-\frac{1}{n}\right)^{nx}& x>0
\end{aligned}
\]
Perhatikan bahwa:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\lim_{n\to\infty}\left(1-\frac{1}{n}\right)^{n}&=e^{-1}\\
\lim_{n\to\infty}\left\{\left(1-\frac{1}{n}\right)^{n}\right\}^x&=e^{-x}\\
\lim_{n\to\infty}\left(1-\frac{1}{n}\right)^{nx}&=e^{-x}
\end{aligned}
\]
Bukti dari:
\[
\begin{aligned}\lim_{n\to\infty}\left( 1 - \frac{1}{n} \right)^n &= \lim_{n\to\infty}\left(\frac{n-1}{n}\right)^n = \lim_{n\to\infty}\left(\frac{1}{\frac{n}{n-1}}\right)^n = \lim_{n\to\infty}\frac{1}{\left(\frac{n}{n-1}\right)^n} \\ &= \lim_{n\to\infty}\frac{1}{\left(1 + \frac{1}{n-1}\right)^n} = \lim_{n\to\infty} \left(\frac{1}{\left(1 + \frac{1}{n-1}\right)^{n-1}} \cdot \frac{1}{1 + \frac{1}{n-1}} \right) \\
&= \lim_{n\to\infty} \frac{1}{\left(1 + \frac{1}{n-1}\right)^{n-1}} = \lim_{n\to\infty} \frac{1}{\left(1 + \frac{1}{n}\right)^{n}} = \frac{1}{e} \\
&= e^{-1}
\end{aligned}
\]
Sehingga:
\[
\lim_{n\to\infty}F_{X_n}(x)=1-e^{-x}, \quad x>0
\]
Yang merupakan fungsi kumulatif dari \(\mathrm{Exponential}(1)\).


Let \(Y_{[1]}\) denote the minimum of a random sample of size n from a distribution that has pdf \(f(x) = e^{-(x-\theta)}, \theta<x< \infty,\) zero elsewhere. Let \(Z_n = n(Y_{[1]} - \theta)\). Investigate the limiting distribution of \(Z_n\)!
Pertama, kaji fungsi kumulatif dari \(Y_1\). Perhatikan bahwa:
\[
\begin{aligned}
F_{Y_{[1]}}(y)=P(Y_{[1]} \leq y)=1-P(Y_{[1]}>y)
\end{aligned}
\]
\(P\left(Y_{[1]}>y\right)\) berarti nilai minimum dari contoh acak tersebut lebih dari nilai tertentu, atau \(y=x\). Namun jika nilai minimum tersebut lebih besar dari \(y=x\), maka pasti semua nilai lebih besar dari \(y=x\). Nilai pertama di sampel, \(Y_1>y\); nilai kedua di sampel, \(Y_2>y\) sampai nilai ke-n \(Y_n>y\) sehingga dapat dibuat:
\[
\begin{aligned}
F_{Y_{[1]}}(y)&=1-P(X_1>x, \ X_2>x, \ldots,X_n>x)&\\
&=1-\left[P(X_1>x)P(X_2>x)\ldots P(X_n>x)\right] & \text{(saling bebas)}\\
&=1-\left[1-F(x)\right]^n
\end{aligned}
\]
Karena \(1-F(x)=1-P(X\leq x)=P(X>x)\). Maka fungsi kumulatif dari \(x\) adalah:
\[
\begin{aligned}
F(x)&=\int_\theta^x e^{-x+\theta}dx=e^\theta\int_\theta^x e^{-x}dx\\
&=e^\theta\left[-e^{-x}\right]^{x}_\theta=e^\theta(-e^{-x}+e^-\theta)\\
&=-e^{-(x-\theta)}+1=1-e^{-(x-\theta)}
\end{aligned}
\]
Maka:
\[
\begin{aligned}
F_{Y_{[1]}}(y)&=1-\left[1-F(x)\right]^n=1-[e^{-n(y-\theta)}]\\
&=1-e^{-n(y-\theta)}
\end{aligned}
\]
Karena fungsi kepekatan peluang adalah turunan dari fungsi kumulatif, maka:
\[
f_{Y_{[1]}}(y)=ne^{-n(y-\theta)}
\]
Sehingga buat transformasi \(Z_n = n(Y_{[1]} - \theta)\):
\[
\begin{aligned}
Z_n &= n(Y_{[1]} - \theta) & \theta<&y_{[1]}<\infty\\
Y_1-\theta &= \frac{Z_n}{n} & 0<&y_{[1]}-\theta<\infty\\
Y_1&=\frac{Z_n}{n}+\theta & 0<&n(y_{[1]}-\theta)<\infty\\
\frac{dy}{dz} &=\frac{1}{n} & 0<&z<\infty
\end{aligned}
\]
Sehingga menurut metode transformasi fungsi:
\[
\begin{aligned}
h(z)&=e^{-z}\\
H(z)&=\int_0^z e^{-z}dz=-e^{-z}+1\\
&=1-e^{-z}
\end{aligned}
\]
Sehingga distribusi tersebut konvergen ke \(\mathrm{Exponential}(1)\).

Konvergensi dalam Distribusi

Diberikan fungsi kumulatif \(X_n\) sebagai berikut. Tunjukkan \(X_{n}\) konvergen dalam distribusi ke \(\mathrm{Exponential}(1)\)!
\[
    \begin{equation}
    F_{X_n}(x)=
    \begin{cases}
    1-\left(1-\frac{1}{n}\right)^{nx} & \quad x > 0\\
    & \quad \\
    0 & \quad \text{lainnya}
    \end{cases}
    \end{equation}
\]


Let \(Y_1\) denote the minimum of a random sample of size n from a distribution that has pdf \(f(x) = e^{-(x-\theta)}, \theta<x< \infty,\) zero elsewhere. Let \(Z_n = n(Y_{1} - \theta)\). Investigate the limiting distribution of \(Z_n\)!

Tentukan fkp/fmp bersama antara \(X_1, X_2, \ldots , X_n\) dan \(\lambda\), \(f(\underline{x},\lambda)\).
Kalikan fungsi massa peluang bersama dan fungsi kepekatan peluang prior:
\[
\begin{aligned}
f\left( \underline{x},\lambda \right) &= f_{\underline{X}}\left( \underline{x} \middle| \lambda \right)\pi(\lambda) = \left( \frac{\lambda^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i}}e^{- n\lambda}}{\prod_{i = 1}^{n}{x_{i}!}} \right)\left( \frac{1}{\Gamma(\alpha)\beta^{\alpha}}\lambda^{\alpha - 1}e^{- \frac{\lambda}{\beta}} \right) \\
&= \frac{\lambda^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha - 1}e^{- \lambda\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)}}{\Gamma(\alpha)\beta^{\alpha}\prod_{i = 1}^{n}{x_{i}!}}
\end{aligned}
\]
Di mana \(x_{i} = 0, 1, 2,\ldots;\ i = 1, 2,\ldots,n\) dan \(\alpha, \beta, \lambda > 0\)

Dari rumus \({\widehat{\lambda}}_{B}\), akan diperoleh penduga Bayes bagi parameter \(\lambda\).
\[
\begin{aligned}
{\widehat{\lambda}}_{B}&= E\left( \lambda \middle| \underline{x} \right) = \int_{\forall\lambda}^{}{\lambda\pi\left( \lambda \middle| \underline{x} \right)}d\lambda = \int_{0}^{\infty}{\lambda\frac{\lambda^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha - 1}e^{- \lambda\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)}\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}}{\Gamma\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)}}d\lambda\\
&=\frac{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}}{\Gamma\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)}\int_{0}^{\infty}{\lambda^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}e^{- \lambda\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)}}d\lambda
\end{aligned}
\]
Lakukan substitusi:
\[
\begin{aligned}
t&=\lambda\left(n+\frac{1}{\beta}\right)\\
dt&=\left(n+\frac{1}{\beta}\right)\ d\lambda
\end{aligned}
\]
\[
\begin{aligned}
{\widehat{\lambda}}_{B}&= \frac{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}}{\Gamma\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)}\int_{0}^{\infty}{\left( \frac{t}{n + \frac{1}{\beta}} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}e^{- t}}\frac{dt}{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)}\\
&=\frac{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}}{\Gamma\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha + 1}}\int_{0}^{\infty}{t^{(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha + 1) - 1}e^{- t}}dt
\end{aligned}
\]
Integral tersebut tak lain merupakan fungsi Gamma sehingga:
\[
\begin{aligned}
{\widehat{\lambda}}_{B}&= \frac{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}\Gamma\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha + 1 \right)}{\Gamma\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)^{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha + 1}}
\end{aligned}
\]
Perhatikan bahwa \(\Gamma(x+1)=x!\), sehingga \(\Gamma(x+1)/\Gamma(x)=x!/(x-1)!=x\):
\[
{\widehat{\lambda}}_{B}= \frac{\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)!}{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha - 1 \right)!} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha}{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)}
\]
Atau, dapat ditemukan dari sifat sebaran:
\[
\begin{aligned}
{\widehat{\lambda}}_{B}&= E\left( \lambda \middle| \underline{x} \right) = {\alpha_p}{\beta_p}= \left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)\left( \frac{\beta}{n\beta + 1} \right)\\
&=\frac{\left( \sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{i} + \alpha \right)}{\left( n + \frac{1}{\beta} \right)}
\end{aligned}
\]
